place.name: WORTHING
place.gazetteerText: WORTHING, a parish in Mitford district, Norfolk; 1½ mile S of Elmham r. station. Post town, Elmham, under Thetford. Acres, 690. Real property, £1,036. Pop., 170. Houses, 34. The manor belongs to the Rev. H. Lombe. The living is a rectory, annexed to Swanton-Morley. The church is good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
